{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 10:47:44.848454", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: backend_web_0, backend_web_1, backend_web_2, host_1_3_1_3, host_2_1_1_4, host_2_2_1_3\n- root_cause_name: ospf_missing_route_advertisement, sender_resource_contention\n\nNotes / rationale:\n- backend_web_0..2 (20.200.0.0/24) showed \"unknown\" reachability and are likely on an isolated, non‑routed backend segment — mapped to ospf_missing_route_advertisement.\n- The three hosts with elevated latency/jitter were included as localized suspicious hosts likely experiencing transient sender-side resource contention — mapped to sender_resource_contention.\n\nIf you want, I can now run the targeted verification steps (check FRR OSPF advertisements, inspect backend interface states, or run repeated pings/traceroutes from the named hosts) to increase confidence and refine remediation steps.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2422, "output_tokens": 214, "total_tokens": 2636, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
